text: Willem Wissing, also known as William Wissing (1656, Amsterdam or The HagueTabitha Barber, ‘Wissing, Willem (1656–1687)’, Oxford Dictionary of National Biography, Oxford University Press, 2004, accessed 30 Dec 2008 \- 10 Sep 1687 Burghley House), was a Dutch portrait artist. He painted many famous people of the day, including William III of England,Mary II of England,Anne of Great Britain. ==References== Category:1656 births Category:1687 deaths Category:Dutch painters
